dc_description_s: Each year, Hennepin County collects 48 hour bicycle counts for sites across either the northern (cycle B) or southern half (cycle A) of the county using MetroCount RoadPod tube counters. This dataset contains the boundaries of the two count zones. For more detailed information on bicycle traffic counts and the latest report, visit https://www.hennepin.us/residents/transportation/biking. Link to Attribute Table Information: http://gis.hennepin.us/OpenData/Metadata/BicycleCountZones.pdf This data (i) is furnished AS IS with no representation as to completeness or accuracy; (ii) is furnished with no warranty of any kind; and (iii) is not suitable for legal, engineering or surveying purposes. Hennepin County shall not be liable for any damage, injury or loss resulting from this data. General questions about this data set, including errors, omissions, corrections and/or updates should be directed to the Hennepin County GIS Office at 612-596-9484.
dc_title_s: Bicycle Count Zones: Hennepin County, Minnesota
